Predict an object of class modeler_HTP

Source: R/10_predict.R
predict.modeler_HTP.Rd

Model predictions for an object of class modeler_HTP

Usage

# S3 method for modeler_HTP
predict(x, time = NULL, plot_id = NULL, ...)

Arguments

x

An object inheriting from class modeler_HTP resulting of executing the function modeler_HTP()

time

A numeric time point to make the prediction. Can be more than one.

plot_id

A numeric to filter by Plot Id.

...

Further parameters. For future improvements.

Value

A data.frame object with predicted values.

Author

Johan Aparicio [aut]

Examples

library(exploreHTP)
data(dt_potato)
results <- read_HTP(
  data = dt_potato,
  genotype = "Gen",
  time = "DAP",
  plot = "Plot",
  traits = c("Canopy", "GLI_2"),
  row = "Row",
  range = "Range"
)
mod <- modeler_HTP(
  x = results,
  index = "Canopy",
  plot_id = 1:2,
  parameters = c(t1 = 45, t2 = 80, k = 0.9),
  fn = "fn_piwise",
  parallel = TRUE
)
mod
#>

#>
